    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-25T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/14966: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vincent</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-25T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 25, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>400. Embassy’s 398, March 19, 9 a.m. Department would appreciate air mail report
                    in regard to economic concessions granted by Sinkiang to Russia<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d171fn43">See telegram No. 534, April 13, 5 p.m., from the Chargé in
                        China, <ref target="#pg_222">p. 222</ref>.</note> mentioned in first
                    paragraph of reference telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
